of power.

04:31.938 --> 04:35.141 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She could get life in prison, if
she's convicted.

04:35.174 --> 04:37.844 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Park was arrested after being
removed from
office.

04:37.877 --> 04:43.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's alleged that she and a
longtime confidant
solicited bribes from businesses
while she

04:43.616 --> 04:45.618 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was president.

04:45.652 --> 04:51.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hundreds of Palestinians in
Israeli prisons
launched a hunger strike today,
in the largest

04:51.291 --> 04:53.459 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
such action in five years.

04:53.493 --> 04:58.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To show their solidarity,
thousands staged
marches in the West Bank and
Gaza.

04:58.464 --> 05:04.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They condemned conditions in the
jails and
the Israeli policy of detention
without trial.

05:04.337 --> 05:08.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): When
prisoners go
on hunger strike, they feel the
freedom.

05:09.008 --> 05:10.910 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is a way to resist.

05:10.943 --> 05:15.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We can win the battle with our
empty stomachs,
and it is a message to the
international community

05:15.214 --> 05:18.785 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the free people in the world
that Palestinians
seek freedom.

05:18.818 --> 05:24.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Israeli officials
say the strike
is politically motivated, and
that it denied

05:24.957 --> 05:27.860 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
-- it also denies that inmates
are being mistreated.

05:27.894 --> 05:34.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Sri Lanka, search teams have
now recovered
at least 29 bodies from a
massive garbage

05:34.500 --> 05:38.104 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
slide that buried dozens of
homes Friday night.

05:38.137 --> 05:44.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, soldiers kept looking in
the huge dump
near Colombo, joined by
relatives of dozens

05:44.277 --> 05:46.112 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of people still missing.

05:46.145 --> 05:50.917 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Crews worked with heavy
equipment to clear
the mud and trash.

05:50.950 --> 05:55.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Newly minted Supreme Court
Justice Neil Gorsuch
heard his first set of arguments
today with

05:55.521 --> 05:57.256 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
fellow justices.

05:57.290 --> 06:01.928 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It was an employment
discrimination case,
and it was only 11 minutes into
the hearing

06:01.961 --> 06:03.863 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
when he asked his first
question.

06:03.896 --> 06:09.302 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At one point, Gorsuch said he
was sorry for
taking up so much time.

06:09.335 --> 06:15.408 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Britain's Prince Harry now says
that he suffered
from repressed grief and
depression for almost

06:15.441 --> 06:19.312 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
20 years after the death of his
mother, Princess
Diana.

06:19.345 --> 06:21.414 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Harry was 12 when she died.

06:21.447 --> 06:23.216 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He's now 32.

06:23.249 --> 06:27.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He tells The Daily Telegraph
that he came
close to what he called a
complete breakdown

06:27.353 --> 06:29.021 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
more than once.

06:29.055 --> 06:34.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says he's now in counseling,
talking openly
about his feelings and doing
better.

06:34.293 --> 06:38.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And president and Mrs. Trump
hosted their
first Easter egg roll at the
White House today.

06:38.998 --> 06:43.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The first couple welcomed the
crowd from the
Truman Balcony for the annual
event that goes

06:43.636 --> 06:45.671 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
back nearly 140 years.

06:45.705 --> 06:50.343 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Later, the president greeted
visitors while
the first lady read to children.

06:50.376 --> 06:53.146 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
More than 21,000 people
attended.

06:53.179 --> 06:56.983 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's actually down from 35,000
last year.

06:57.016 --> 07:01.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
what's next
for U.S. policy toward North
Korea after the

07:01.587 --> 07:07.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
