him and seeks to intimidate the
other half

20:19.685 --> 20:21.420 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the country.

20:21.453 --> 20:26.825 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There are allegations of
electoral -- questionable
electoral practices, I should
say.

20:26.858 --> 20:30.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the opposition is calling
for an investigation
into it.

20:30.495 --> 20:35.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's unlikely that anything is
going to change,
but it does suggest a deepening
of the polarization

20:35.500 --> 20:37.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Turkish society.

20:37.302 --> 20:40.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, does it
suggest -- do
you see going forward that he
will have to

20:40.973 --> 20:45.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
now reach out to opponents to be
more accommodating
or less so?

20:45.644 --> 20:50.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KADIR USTUN: Look, he has tried
many times
at parliamentary commission to
draft a whole

20:50.616 --> 20:56.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
new civilian constitution,
failed because
of political realities.

20:56.088 --> 21:02.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this was the product of a
deal between
the opposition nationalist
party, MHP, and

21:02.527 --> 21:10.402 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the A.K. party, and I don't see
this as changing
the system wholesale in a
desirable way.

21:10.435 --> 21:14.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But what I'm
asking is, what
do you see changing the stance
of President

21:14.339 --> 21:15.307 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Erdogan?

21:15.340 --> 21:16.842 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Does he reach out to opponents?

21:16.875 --> 21:20.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is he more accommodating to all
Turks, or
tougher?

21:20.846 --> 21:26.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KADIR USTUN: When you look at
the Turkish
political landscape, you see
identity policies,

21:26.318 --> 21:33.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
these parties, Kurdish party,
nationalist
party, and CHP, are consolidated
, just as

21:33.625 --> 21:35.093 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
A.K.

21:35.127 --> 21:38.463 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Party's votes are more or less
consolidated.

21:38.497 --> 21:43.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have that kind of situation
in the Turkish
political landscape.

21:43.735 --> 21:46.605 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that won't change all that
much.

21:46.638 --> 21:51.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we're going to see in 2019,
when you have
the presidential and the general
elections

21:51.610 --> 21:57.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
held on the same day, if there
will be significant
changes.

21:57.182 --> 22:02.521 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I don't expect those votes
to change all
that much in the next election.

22:02.554 --> 22:07.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And what about
the Turkish
relationship with the West,
especially the

22:07.059 --> 22:08.026 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
U.S.?

22:08.060 --> 22:09.928 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What should the response be from
the U.S.?

22:09.961 --> 22:13.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN COOK: Well, there's a
difference between
what should the response be and
what the reality

22:13.231 --> 22:15.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is likely to be.

22:15.067 --> 22:19.971 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think that the Obama
administration over
the course of eight years was
too quiet about

22:20.005 --> 22:24.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the excesses of Prime Minister
and then President
Erdogan and the deepening
authoritarianism

22:24.876 --> 22:26.812 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Turkey.

22:26.845 --> 22:31.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It strikes me that President
Trump will accommodate
himself to this outcome, because
his priorities

22:31.717 --> 22:33.752 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lie with fighting the Islamic
State.

22:33.785 --> 22:37.789 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, of course, the United
States looks to
Turkey as an ally in that fight.

22:37.823 --> 22:40.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And, briefly,
what do you think
the U.S. response should be and
Europe?

22:41.026 --> 22:46.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KADIR USTUN: In relations with
the U.S. particularly
-- that's what I'm focused on --
there are

22:46.365 --> 22:54.673 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
significant strategic
differences, especially
with the U.S. support for the
YPG in Northern

22:54.706 --> 23:00.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Syria, the groups that are
fighting ISIS,
and that -- they are linked to
PKK.

23:00.078 --> 23:06.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's a significant problem
in U.S.-Turkey
relations and on several other
relations.

23:06.051 --> 23:09.755 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I think both sides will need
Trump administration.

23:09.788 --> 23:12.624 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Turks see Trump administration
as a new opportunity.

23:12.657 --> 23:15.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they will need to talk more
on this.

23:15.293 --> 23:16.728 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And there have been talks.

23:16.762 --> 23:19.731 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we see the lessening of
those tensions.

23:19.765 --> 23:25.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the coming years, I do expect
that to move
to a better place.

23:25.437 --> 23:32.911 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But in terms of this
authoritarianism argument,
I find it overly simplistic and
sort of easy

23:32.944 --> 23:35.280 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
explanation, oh, Turkey is
authoritarian.

23:35.313 --> 23:42.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That doesn't answer the question
about why
50 percent are voting for this
party and Erdogan.

23:42.120 --> 23:45.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, we
will leave it
there and we will watch going
forward.

23:45.290 --> 23:51.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kadir Ustun and Steven Cook,
thank you both
very much.

23:51.263 --> 23:54.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
STEVEN COOK: Thank you.

23:54.332 --> 23:57.369 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
KADIR USTUN: Thank you.

23:57.402 --> 24:03.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us,
coming up on
the "NewsHour": a murder posted
online, a

24:03.608 --> 24:11.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
killer still at large; and a
world in disarray,
a selection from the "NewsHour"
Bookshelf.

24:11.883 --> 24:16.321 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But first: an unlikely
innovation from an
unusual innovator.

24:16.354 --> 24:21.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Fred de
Sam Lazaro has
the story of one man who has
made it his mission

24:21.660 --> 24:25.730 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to bring affordable hygiene
products to women
in India.

24:25.764 --> 24:28.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Its part of our series Agents
for Change.

24:28.433 --> 24:34.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Arunachalam
Muruganantham
says he was a born tinkerer,
obsessed with

24:34.072 --> 24:38.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
figuring out how things worked,
from toys
to bicycles.

24:38.076 --> 24:42.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He grew up in poverty after his
father died
young, dropped out of school and
became a

24:42.581 --> 24:44.449 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
welder, a lower-middle-class
occupation in
India.

24:44.483 --> 24:47.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM,
Inventor: To support
my mother, I stop my schooling.

24:47.953 --> 24:52.023 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: But his
natural curiosity
apparently knew no bounds.

24:52.057 --> 24:59.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Years later, it took him into a
strictly taboo
area in India's tradition-bound
society: menstrual

24:59.164 --> 25:00.665 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
hygiene.

25:00.699 --> 25:03.668 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: We
are able to
break the taboo, and using it.

25:03.702 --> 25:07.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He's become
known as India's
pad man.

25:07.606 --> 25:13.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Your goal is to have every woman
in this country
use sanitary pads, if they need
it?

25:13.812 --> 25:15.547 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: Yes,
it's a movement.

25:15.580 --> 25:19.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: A movement
begun by a
man who knew almost nothing
about the female

25:19.618 --> 25:21.987 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
body until after he was married.

25:22.020 --> 25:25.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You didn't even know what
menstruation at
all.

25:25.123 --> 25:27.025 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You had no idea what it was.

25:27.058 --> 25:28.793 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is that correct?

25:28.827 --> 25:30.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: Yes,
I don't know
when it is happening, how it is
happening,

25:30.762 --> 25:32.264 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
even why it is happening.

25:32.297 --> 25:34.065 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I don't know.

25:34.099 --> 25:36.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: And, he
says, his wife,
Shanthi, wasn't particularly
interested in

25:37.002 --> 25:38.103 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
discussing it.

25:38.136 --> 25:40.238 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: It's
the biggest
taboo.

25:40.272 --> 25:41.540 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Wife never talks to husband.

25:41.573 --> 25:43.074 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Daughter never talks to mother.

25:43.108 --> 25:47.078 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: That comes
at a high cost
in public health.

25:47.112 --> 25:51.983 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some experts say millions of
girls across
the developing world miss school
during their

25:52.017 --> 25:58.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
periods and remain susceptible
to infection
throughout adulthood.

25:58.690 --> 26:03.962 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Sanitary pads are widely
advertised in India,
but surveys suggest only about
one in 10 women

26:03.995 --> 26:05.530 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
actually uses them.

26:05.564 --> 26:08.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
At first, Muruganantham
suggested them to
his wife.

26:08.099 --> 26:11.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: I
asked simply,
there is some products in the
market.

26:11.770 --> 26:13.772 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Why you're not using that?

26:13.805 --> 26:18.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She instantly told, I also know
about that,
but we have to cut our family
milk budget.

26:18.877 --> 26:19.945 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Milk budget?

26:19.978 --> 26:20.946 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: Yes.

26:20.979 --> 26:23.315 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then I find it's a matter of
affordability.

26:23.348 --> 26:28.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He could
afford one package
of sanitary pads and gave it to
Shanthi as

26:28.286 --> 26:32.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a gift, partly to find out how
they were made
and why they had to be so
expensive.

26:32.991 --> 26:35.827 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: The
white substance
inside is a cotton.

26:35.860 --> 26:39.531 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The raw material cost of the
cotton is a few
pennies.

26:39.564 --> 26:42.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I bought the product for
dollars.

26:42.167 --> 26:48.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, even being illiterate, I
thought, why
not try to make an affordable
pad for my wife?

26:48.039 --> 26:52.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Over the
next few years,
he tried, using local cotton, to
replicate

26:52.344 --> 26:54.045 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the commercial pads.

26:54.079 --> 26:59.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His wife suffered through early
prototypes
that didn't work and went back
to using a

26:59.084 --> 27:00.919 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
rag.

27:00.952 --> 27:04.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Muruganantham then coaxed some
female medical
students to try his subsequent
models, figuring

27:04.823 --> 27:07.792 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the future doctors would be less
shy.

27:07.826 --> 27:13.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he even began wearing a pad
himself, creating
an artificial uterus and rubber
bladder, coaxing

27:13.999 --> 27:18.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a local butcher to provide the
raw material,
and testing it out while he rode
a bicycle.

27:18.970 --> 27:21.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: I
filled goat blood,
animal blood in it.

27:21.740 --> 27:22.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I tied on my hip.

27:23.008 --> 27:25.443 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is a tube connection to
the napkin and
the bladder.

27:25.477 --> 27:27.545 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Shanthi had
had enough.

27:27.579 --> 27:30.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHANTHI MURUGANANTHAM, Wife of
Arunachalam
Muruganantham (through
translator): Everyone

27:30.148 --> 27:32.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the village was saying he'd
gone off his
head.

27:32.450 --> 27:33.852 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I was truly afraid.

27:33.885 --> 27:36.454 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
People said he had become like a
vampire,
that he was doing crazy things.

27:36.488 --> 27:40.291 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: She
asked me to,
"I want to go my parents' home
for a few days."

27:40.325 --> 27:41.426 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She never came back.

27:41.459 --> 27:43.962 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And third month, I got a divorce
notice from
my wife.

27:43.995 --> 27:45.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: She filed
for divorce?

27:45.864 --> 27:46.831 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: Yes.

27:46.865 --> 27:48.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I got a divorce notice.

27:48.333 --> 27:51.503 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: His mother,
who lived
in the home, also left him.

27:51.536 --> 27:53.738 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But his curiosity didn't leave
him.

27:53.772 --> 27:59.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He called an American supplier
posing as an
industrialist in his hometown of
Coimbatore

27:59.144 --> 28:01.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
looking to branch out into
feminine hygiene
products.

28:01.880 --> 28:06.217 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: Then
I claim myself,
I'm a mill owner in Coimbatore.

28:06.251 --> 28:08.019 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Please send some samples.

28:08.053 --> 28:11.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The samples
arrived and,
one day, when he wasn't home,
his dog tore

28:11.756 --> 28:12.891 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
into them.

28:12.924 --> 28:14.359 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: She
took the courier
cover.

28:14.392 --> 28:15.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She scratches it.

28:15.794 --> 28:18.730 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Oh, my God, I saw the secret:
the fiber.

28:18.763 --> 28:20.298 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You can see the fiber.

28:20.331 --> 28:24.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: So, the dog
opened this
for you?

28:24.135 --> 28:25.103 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM:
Opened it.

28:25.136 --> 28:27.205 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She scratches it with the anger.

28:27.238 --> 28:31.876 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: It was
cellulose, he discovered,
that, when scratched vigorously,
becomes sponge-like

28:31.910 --> 28:33.745 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and highly absorbent.

28:33.778 --> 28:38.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It took two years to perfect a
machine to
fluff up the cellulose, he said,
a modified

28:38.616 --> 28:42.220 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
food blender in which the blades
have to be
angled just so.

28:42.253 --> 28:45.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: It
got a prestigious
award from Indian Institute of
Technology

28:45.156 --> 28:47.125 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as the best innovation.

28:47.158 --> 28:51.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: It's simple,
easily replicated,
and can be modified to work
without electricity,

28:51.663 --> 28:53.164 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
he says.

28:53.198 --> 28:58.303 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The pads can be made and sold
for a fraction
of the commercial varieties.

28:58.336 --> 29:03.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is the model for how
Muruganantham would
like to see his product
distributed, thousands

29:03.341 --> 29:08.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of small factories run by groups
of women
producing these sanitary pads at
very low

29:08.480 --> 29:11.483 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
cost and selling them directly
to women.

29:11.516 --> 29:15.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Women are far more comfortable
buying the
pads from women directly, rather
than from

29:15.787 --> 29:17.756 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a store, Muruganantham says.

29:17.789 --> 29:21.126 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Feminine hygiene is not
discussed in open
company.

29:21.159 --> 29:26.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our own questions elicited
nervous laughter
from the very women making them,
even as they

29:26.264 --> 29:27.832 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
praised their product.

29:27.866 --> 29:30.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHANTI UDAYKUMAR, Factory Worker
(through
translator): There's definitely
benefit.

29:30.301 --> 29:33.772 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Before, we were using only
cloth, and it was
very difficult.

29:33.805 --> 29:35.340 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now girls don't have that
difficulty.

29:35.373 --> 29:38.209 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was much easier for them than
it was for
us.

29:38.243 --> 29:42.747 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO:
Muruganantham is determined
to change this.

29:42.781 --> 29:47.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ARUNACHALAM MURUGANANTHAM: I
want to make
this as a low-cost sanitary pad
movement across

29:47.552 --> 29:49.387 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the globe.

29:49.420 --> 29:52.891 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Helped by
awards and his
own advocacy, more than 4,000
small factories

29:52.924 --> 29:58.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have started making his sanitary
